    "content": "<p>Went for a walk in the Jufferswaard and Noordberg, a glacial-induced valley and moraine, to the south of Heelsum (and Renkum) and north of the Nether-Rhine.</p>\r\n<figure class=\"center\"><img src=\"/kd/images/notes/2026/06-29/PXL_20260629_110654550.jpg\" class=\"u-photo\" alt=\"Cows cooling down in between the jetties of the Nether Rhine\"></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"center\"><img src=\"/kd/images/notes/2026/06-29/PXL_20260629_110804228.jpg\" class=\"u-photo\" alt=\"Picknick table atop the Noordberg, overlooking the Rhine, the village of Heteren and very far in the distance, the city of Nijmegen.\"></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"center\"><img src=\"/kd/images/notes/2026/06-29/PXL_20260629_111757492.jpg\" class=\"u-photo\" alt=\"Wheat field with cornflowers\"></figure>\r\n<figure class=\"center\"><img src=\"/kd/images/notes/2026/06-29/PXL_20260629_112633138.jpg\" class=\"u-photo\" alt=\"Backside of a Church in Heelsum, called Kerkje Op De Heuvel (Little Church on the Hill)\"></figure>",
